description._content: The Explorer's Pavilion, a memorial erected in 1913 at Mt. York, as part of the centenary celebrations of the first European crossing of the Blue Mountains. This image is part of a collection entitled ‘Blue Mountains - Monuments and Celebrations', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection. If you have more accurate information regarding the location and/or date of the image, we would love to hear from you!
